 Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Oughtred Sir was born in 1250, in Scarborough, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son. He died on 24 May 1310, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1250–24 May 1310":"1250–24. mai 1310","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1250–1310":"1250–1310","24 May 1310":"24. mai 1310","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1250":"1250","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1250–24 May 1310":"1250–24. toukokuuta 1310","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1250–1310":"1250–1310","24 May 1310":"24. toukokuuta 1310","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1250":"1250","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1250–24 May 1310":"1250–24 mai 1310","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1250–1310":"1250–1310","24 May 1310":"24 mai 1310","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1250":"1250","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Oughtred Sir est né en 1250, à Scarborough, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé le 24 mai 1310, à l’âge de 60 ans."},"de":{"1250–24 May 1310":"1250–24. Mai 1310","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1250–1310":"1250–1310","24 May 1310":"24. Mai 1310","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","1250":"1250","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert Oughtred Sir wurde 1250 in Scarborough, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb am 24. Mai 1310 im Alter von 60 Jahren."},"ht":{"1250–24 May 1310":"1